Q-Med Inc said preliminary resultsshow its second quarter, ended May 31, revenues exceeded 4.2mln dlrs. A year earlier revenues were nearly 1.4 mln dlrs.    The company also said it had appointed Coopers and Lybrandas its auditors. Chairman Michael Cox declined any comment onthis appointment.    The company said its preliminary second quarter revenuesare consistent with management's expectations and represent agreater than 40 pct increase in sales over those reported forthe first quarter. Earnings should show a similar growthpattern, the company added. Reuter&#3;